==English==
===Etymology===
{{Gr.}} ''tri-'' three; ''meros'' part
===Adjective===
'''trimerous'''
#{{botany}} in three parts: in a flower each whorl (of flower parts) has three flower parts. 
:''The monocots will typically have trimerous flowers.''

